parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front strut housing can cause the steering wheel to jerk or vibrate, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel jerks or vibrates
the vehicle pulls to one side
the strut tower is rusted or broken
the steering column is difficult to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to lock up or become difficult to turn, making it impossible to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel locks up
the steering column is difficult to turn
the steering wheel jerks or vibrates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition key can prevent the vehicle from starting, leaving the driver stranded, which can be a safety issue, especially in remote areas or extreme weather conditions.
symptoms: The ignition key does not rotate
the vehicle cannot start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of vehicle components, such as the strut tower, can cause the steering column to fail, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the strut tower
fenders
or other vehicle components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of front suspension components can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and can also lead to brake failure, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle.
symptoms: Rattling and squeaking noises
vibration
knocking noise from the left front of the vehicle
brake failure
excessive corrosion on the front passenger side suspension affecting the brake lines and frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the strut tower housing can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and can also lead to brake failure, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle.
symptoms: Rattling and squeaking noises
vibration
knocking noise from the left front of the vehicle
brake failure
excessive corrosion on the front passenger side suspension affecting the brake lines and frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the rear track arm bushing can cause the rear end of the vehicle to shake side to side, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Rear end of the vehicle shakes side to side
especially when not under load from the gas pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Frame Corrosion and Structural Integrity Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion and structural failures of the frame can lead to loss of vehicle control, increased risk of accidents, and potential injuries due to detached or falling components.
symptoms: Clanking metallic sounds
rust or corrosion on the frame
detachment of strut towers or running boards
sagging or falling off of running boards
warning lights illuminating (e.g.
ABS)
and inability to open doors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the doors to open can lead to entrapment, increased risk of accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: Inability to open rear exterior and interior doors.
